  "design_pillars": [
    "This is a forest map, not a river map: no rivers, bridges, mountains, or water chokepoints.",
    "The maze is made from forest density, clearings, roads, fallen trees, ridges, and prop-readable landmarks.",
    "No road crosses any hill. Roads bend around hills and connect to hill entrances, lookout edges, villages, neutral barracks, and flanking lanes.",
    "The center is valuable but not mandatory. Players can contest the shrine ridge, capture a neutral lodge, raid through forest trails, or pressure the enemy base through outer roads.",
    "Two neutral barracks create side-objective tension without adding extra active empires."
  ],
