      }
    ]
  },
  "mission_balance": {
    "intended_match_duration_minutes": [22, 38],
    "balance_notes": [
      "Symmetry is rotational: player 1 has faster access to south lodge, player 2 has faster access to north lodge.",
      "The central shrine is strong but has four entrance pockets and two ring roads, so it should not become a single unbeatable choke.",
      "Neutral barracks should be valuable but not mandatory; capturing one gives tempo, capturing both risks overextension.",
      "Catapults prefer the wider default roads; rough cutpaths should slow or discourage siege movement.",
      "Dense forests create ambush opportunities, while clearings around bases and center keep major fights readable."
    ],
